GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2901121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kampala Radio Uganda Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The exercise of ferrying NRA [National 
Resistance Army] troops on a peacekeeping mission to Liberia has 
ended with the last batch of 95 officers and men leaving Entebbe 
International Airport aboard a UN aircraft this morning. 
  Today's contingent, which included 10 military police 
personnel, brings the number of Ugandan peace keepers in Liberia 
to 767, based in Kakata, Buchanaland, about 25 miles outside the 
city of Monrovia. [passage omitted]. 

