<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Renamo Official Accuses Government of Infiltration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0102112594 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0700 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0102112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jose de Castro, Mozambique National Resistance's 
[Renamo] foreign secretary, said his movement does not agree 
with the salary payment increments beacuse they only benefit a 
minority group. Jose de Castro, who was speaking after a long 
tour of the country, said the government is infiltrating State 
Information and Security Service elements into the Renamo 
provincial delegations with the aim of destabilizing the 
movement. The Renamo secretary for foreign affairs said his 
party's militants are being demoted, transferred, or even 
expelled from the state apparatus and companies. 

</TEXT>

