<H3> <TI>   Velayati Receives Bulgarian Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0202080794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0202080794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Dr. Velayati met the Bulgarian 
prime minister in Sofia last night. Lyuben Berov described 
Velayati's visit to Bulgaria as a turning point for improving 
and strengthening the bases of bilateral relations. He stressed 
his government's eagerness to increase commercial exchanges with 
Iran. 
  He expressed interest in purchasing gas and oil from the 
Islamic Republic of Iran and called for greater facilities to 
broaden commercial relations between Tehran and Sofia. 
  Stressing the consolidation of mutual friendship and 
reciprocal trust, Dr. Velayati said that activating the two 
countries' private sectors, joint investment, and cooperation in 
free trade zones was very important for upgrading relations. 
  According to IRNA, the Bulgarian prime minister said he was 
grateful that President Hashemi-Rafsanjani was safe following 
yesterday's shooting incident at the mausoleum of the imam, may 
God be pleased with him. 

</TEXT>

