<H3> <TI>   Security Council Issues Statement on `Plot' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0202072694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0202072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following the plot by a limited number of 
counterrevolutionaries on Tuesday who had congregated in one of 
the streets in Zahedan and intended to create agitation and 
disturbances, the Secretariat of the Supreme National Security 
Council issued a statement last night, the text of which is as 
follows: 
  A number of elements who--in the course of the measures 
taken 
by the security forces of the Islamic Republic of Iran in the 
eastern border areas of the country--perceived that they could 
attain their lost interests congregated in one of the streets in 
Zahedan. They broke the windows of some residential buildings 
and damaged some vehicles passing on the streets, including 
those of the law enforcement forces. In performing their 
legitimate duties and in order to restore law and order, the law 
enforcement forces therefore intervened and began dispersing 
these people and arresting the disruptive elements. 

</TEXT>

