<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic, Finance Minister Meets World Bank Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3001141594 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3001141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mohammad-Khan, minister for economic affairs and 
finance, in a meeting with a delegation from the World Bank, 
spoke about the significant and fundamental role of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran in the region. 
  Mohammad-Khan said: The main indexes obtained during the 
first development plan indicate that the country's economy is 
moving toward an organized and programmed economy -- and taking 
into account the world economic recession, Iran enjoys a 
relatively good growth. 
  Referring to the substitution of imports that will reduce 
future foreign currency requirements, he said: With the 
increase in domestic production, there will be a fall in the 
import of petrochemical goods and foods, as well as commodities 
needed by consumer and intermediate industries while the export 
of nonoil goods will increase. 
  Mohammad-Khan also spoke on the policy of privatization and 
said the government intends to sell factories through auction or 
limited partnership with individuals interested in investment 
and management. 
  The minister for economic affairs and finance also spoke on 
Iran's important role of creating positive prospects for 
neighboring countries' economies, as well as creating provisions 
for transport of goods from Iranian ports. 

</TEXT>

