<H3> <TI>   Government Team to CCF Wants Soldiers Demobilized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0302103694 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0400 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0302103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Mozambican Government team to the Cease-Fire 
Commission [CCF] has asked the CCF chairman to ensure that the 
date for the beginning of the demobilization process be set as 
soon as possible. In a note it sent to the Radio Mozambique 
news desk, the government team to the CSC has said that soldiers 
confined to the assembly areas that opened in December have 
already been there for more than eight weeks, adding that that 
is much too long. 

</TEXT>

