Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Dr. Brazao Mazula has been unanimously elected 
chairman of the National Elections Commission [CNE]. Brazao 
Mazula, aged 49, is married and comes from Lichinga, Niassa 
Province. He has a doctorate in history and education, a 
master's degree in education sciences, and an honors degree in 
philosophy and theology. He was a Catholic priest for four 
years before occupying top posts at various levels in the 
Education Ministry. 
