<H3> <TI>   ANC Supporters Demand Removal of Assembly Nominees </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0402131994 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0402131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] ANC [African National Congress] supporters have 
slammed the nomination of former House of Delegates Chairman 
J.N. Reddy to the ANC's list of candidates to the National 
Assembly. A mass meeting in Durban, called by the Natal Indian 
Congress to explain the reasons behind the nomination, failed to 
convince the ANC supporters. They demanded that Dr. Reddy and 
former Natal MEC [Member Executive Committee], D.S. Rajah, be 
removed from the list on the grounds that they had been part of 
an oppressive system that had played no role in making life 
better for the masses. Dr. Reddy will make an announcement on 
his nomination today. 

</TEXT>

