Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] While peace is being negotiated in Lusaka, Zambia, 
Eduardo dos Santos' men continue to decimate innocent civilians 
in the Huila and Benguela Provinces. According to correspondent 
Silva Aleluia, terrible crimes are being committed by the 
Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor Party 
[MPLA-PT], particularly in the Chongoroi and Caimbambo 
Districts. The People's Armed Forces for the Liberation of 
Angola [FAPLA] have been carying out acts of murder, violating 
[words indistinct], and stealing people's goods. At least 223 
people have been massacred in these areas since December last 
year. Silva Aleluia learned this from Colonel Catu, from the 
UNITA Armed Forces Command in the Southeastern Region. 

