<H3> <TI>   Customs Officials End Strike 3 Feb; Demands Met </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0302153094 Dakar PANA in English 1159 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0302153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Dakar PANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Niamey, 3 Feb (ANP/PANA)--The 850 Niger customs 
officers who went on strike on Monday [31 January] to press 
demands for better working conditions are to resume work from 
Thursday. The strike ended after their demands, which also 
included the reemployment of some of their colleagues who had 
been declared redundant, had been met. The general secretary of 
the National Union of Customs Officers (SNAD), Lt Ibro Ayouba, 
in a statement on Wednesday evening asked customs officers to 
resume work. He said a follow-up committee had been formed to 
implement measures promised by the government at the 
negotiations. 

</TEXT>

