Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Somalia: Gino Del Nero, a rescue worker working for 
the Italian NGO, CISP, the International Committee for the 
Development of Peoples, was kidnapped this morning at Dusa 
Mareb, 300 km east of Mogadishu, where the organization has a 
base for rescue operations. It has been reported that Del Nero 
was kidnapped as he was returning to the base. The kidnappers 
reportedly asked for a $10,000 ransom. 

